01:06.816 --> 01:10.153
♪ Got 'em like, Oh, my Lord ♪

01:10.195 --> 01:13.281
Simone: Hey, Jordan.
Um, it's me.

01:13.323 --> 01:17.619
I heard about
what happened and...

01:17.660 --> 01:21.122
I just wanted to call and say
that I'm really sorry.

01:21.164 --> 01:24.876
I'm here,
me and your Bringston fam.

01:24.918 --> 01:27.420
Um, we're here for you
and for Liv, so...

01:28.838 --> 01:30.090
yeah.

01:31.883 --> 01:32.967
Bye.

01:39.307 --> 01:42.602
I just wish there was more
that I could say and do.

01:43.978 --> 01:47.398
I know, but
how are you?

01:48.566 --> 01:50.151
I am.

01:55.198 --> 01:56.699
I just need to focus

01:56.741 --> 01:59.661
on getting Keisha's
choreography down, so...

01:59.702 --> 02:01.204
We're
working nonstop...

02:01.246 --> 02:03.331
trying to get
this ball together,

02:03.373 --> 02:05.125
and each pledge
has to host

02:05.166 --> 02:07.293
an alumni that's in town
for the event.

02:07.335 --> 02:09.170
How have things been
with Damon?

02:09.212 --> 02:11.756
You know, since the
"Let's be friends" gate?

02:11.798 --> 02:14.008
Fine.

02:14.050 --> 02:15.510
Everything is fine.

02:15.552 --> 02:16.761
Mm-hmm.

02:16.803 --> 02:18.346
[Knock on door]

02:21.766 --> 02:23.226
Nathaniel Hardin,

02:23.268 --> 02:24.602
you have
a special delivery

02:24.644 --> 02:26.938
from the Black and Red
Masquerade Ball.

02:26.980 --> 02:28.439
OK. Period.

02:30.441 --> 02:33.236
Oh, I'm loving whatever
that was. [Chuckles]

02:33.278 --> 02:35.613
Fundraiser for
the Masquerade Ball.

02:35.655 --> 02:37.574
So, your date
can get you a gift,

02:37.615 --> 02:39.868
a note, or whatever.

02:39.909 --> 02:42.453
Well, looks like
I got a letter.

02:43.705 --> 02:45.957
"Roses are red,
violets are blue,

02:45.999 --> 02:47.667
"I'll see you at the dance,

02:47.709 --> 02:50.378
I'll be the gentleman
in blue."

02:50.420 --> 02:51.880
Doesn't say
who it's from.

02:51.921 --> 02:53.840
Hmm. Well,
it sounds to me

02:53.882 --> 02:56.009
like you got a little
secret admirer.

02:56.050 --> 02:58.720
[Snaps fingers]
♪ Get it, get it, uh! ♪

03:00.972 --> 03:03.183
Hey, bro.
Check this out.

03:03.224 --> 03:05.518
Vintage stretch limo.
We showin' up
and showin' out

03:05.560 --> 03:08.188
to the masquerade ball
in style.

03:08.229 --> 03:10.690
About that.
I'm not going.

03:10.732 --> 03:12.734
But I'll still
give you my half.

03:12.775 --> 03:15.195
Look, I appreciate that,
but what's with you
canceling last minute?

03:15.236 --> 03:16.863
Well, when we made
the plans,

03:16.905 --> 03:18.406
I was with Thea.

03:18.448 --> 03:20.116
Now I'm not.

03:20.158 --> 03:21.618
I mean,
I'm not with anybody.

03:21.659 --> 03:24.412
So, don't feel like
third-wheeling.

03:24.454 --> 03:26.456
Oh. We can
find you a date.

03:26.497 --> 03:29.626
Ah. Nah, thank you.
I'm good, bro.

03:29.667 --> 03:31.586
But look--have fun
at the masquerade ball.

03:31.628 --> 03:33.213
Probably be lit.

03:37.300 --> 03:39.928
OK. Gonna get him a date.

03:46.351 --> 03:48.478
Marcus: OK, everybody's
gearing up for
the masquerade ball.

03:48.519 --> 03:50.188
It's a shame that we
missed out on our moment

03:50.230 --> 03:51.814
when we were
students here.

03:51.856 --> 03:54.651
When the minors call,
you gotta answer.

03:54.692 --> 03:57.111
My dress, though,
was to die for.

03:57.153 --> 03:59.239
[Both chuckle]
Yes.

03:59.280 --> 04:00.740
Any word from HR?

04:00.782 --> 04:02.951
As a matter of fact,
they said

04:02.992 --> 04:04.869
as long as our
personal relationship

04:04.911 --> 04:06.412
pre-dated
our business one...

04:06.454 --> 04:08.122
Which it does.

04:08.164 --> 04:10.083
dating shouldn't
be an issue.

04:10.124 --> 04:13.962
But it's the optics
that still worry me.

04:14.003 --> 04:15.922
Look, you know,
we're getting ahead
of ourselves.

04:15.964 --> 04:17.715
We don't even know
where this is going.

04:17.757 --> 04:21.344
We haven't even dated
in, like, 17 years.

04:21.386 --> 04:23.930
So, maybe
we start there.

04:23.972 --> 04:26.224
A date could be nice.

04:26.266 --> 04:27.517
Tomorrow.

04:27.558 --> 04:28.893
OK.

04:29.978 --> 04:32.272
Leave everything
up to me.

04:34.691 --> 04:36.985
Thea: Hey. I'm not
sure what the rule is

04:37.026 --> 04:39.529
with exes and jewelry,

04:39.570 --> 04:42.115
but I just thought
I should give this
back to you.

04:42.156 --> 04:45.910
Yeah, uh...Thea,
this is my bad.

04:45.952 --> 04:47.787
No, no. For real.
Um...

04:47.829 --> 04:50.331
like, I put this
in place when we
were together

04:50.373 --> 04:54.168
and forgot to
cancel it after we--

04:54.210 --> 04:58.256
No, I figured. But
the necklace is stunning.

04:58.298 --> 04:59.841
You did really good.

04:59.882 --> 05:01.926
Thanks.

05:01.968 --> 05:05.138
Look, I don't know
the rules on...

05:05.179 --> 05:07.181
exes and jewelry
either,

05:07.223 --> 05:09.767
but my rule is if
I get you something,

05:09.809 --> 05:11.519
well, you keep it.

05:11.561 --> 05:13.229
No. I can't.

05:13.271 --> 05:15.106
Look, Thea, I insist.

05:15.148 --> 05:17.650
Really, it's yours, like,
and whenever you wear it,

05:17.692 --> 05:21.487
I know you'll
look amazing in it.

05:22.655 --> 05:23.781
Thank you.

05:26.784 --> 05:29.829
All right. Uh,
I'll see you around.

05:29.871 --> 05:31.914
OK. See ya.

05:33.374 --> 05:34.667
[Cell phone chimes]

05:49.390 --> 05:50.767
Sorry I'm late.

05:52.560 --> 05:54.479
Thea, you good?

05:54.520 --> 05:57.899
Not anymore. Um...

05:57.940 --> 05:59.192
well...

06:02.028 --> 06:04.447
Man: Is that you?
Thea: Mm-hmm.

06:04.489 --> 06:06.282
Who is the little
girl next to you?

06:06.324 --> 06:09.118
Grand Slam winner
Iris McDonald.

06:09.160 --> 06:11.162
Yeah, and that's me
beating her.

06:11.204 --> 06:12.872
I didn't even
remember that

06:12.914 --> 06:15.249
until my mom found this.

06:15.291 --> 06:17.502
Wow. Huh.
That's dope.

06:17.543 --> 06:20.046
She's a world champion,
and I'm here

06:20.088 --> 06:22.757
talking to you.
No offense.

06:22.799 --> 06:25.385
None taken.
I get it.

06:25.426 --> 06:27.178
Look, I'm graduating,

06:27.220 --> 06:29.722
and I'll be hitting
the pro circuit soon.

06:29.764 --> 06:33.017
You are a sophomore
coming back from a injury
stronger than ever.

06:33.059 --> 06:35.686
So, maybe you getting
that photo is a sign.

06:35.728 --> 06:37.188
That I should go pro?

06:37.230 --> 06:38.815
Yes. Sign up
for a Challenger.

06:38.856 --> 06:40.566
See how you stack up
against the pros.

06:40.608 --> 06:42.819
Yeah, but if I do that,
I'd essentially be saying

06:42.860 --> 06:44.404
that I'm leaving
the Bringston team.

06:44.445 --> 06:46.531
And what's
the alternative?

06:46.572 --> 06:49.367
Stay here and talk about
your glory days when
you beat a champion?

06:55.289 --> 06:56.916
Uh, Ms. Morgan?

06:56.958 --> 06:59.585
Hi. I'm Simone Hicks,

06:59.627 --> 07:01.295
and on behalf of PKZ,

07:01.337 --> 07:02.505
I'll be your host
this weekend.

07:02.547 --> 07:04.590
It's nice to
meet you, Simone.

07:04.632 --> 07:06.634
Nice to meet you, too.
Uh, I'll be at
your disposal 24/7,

07:06.676 --> 07:08.219
so, if there's anything
that you'll need

07:08.261 --> 07:11.556
when you're on campus,
just, you know.

07:11.597 --> 07:13.975
Off the jump, I do
need a few things.

07:14.016 --> 07:17.687
For you to call me Charlotte
and for you to relax.

07:17.728 --> 07:19.480
I know your dean of
pledges told you

07:19.522 --> 07:21.274
to cater to
my every need,

07:21.315 --> 07:23.776
but I won't be able
to see if you're
truly PKZ material

07:23.818 --> 07:25.945
if you're running my errands
and carrying my bags.

07:25.987 --> 07:30.825
OK. Period.
So, how do we start?

07:30.867 --> 07:35.455
With coffee and with you
telling me about you
and where you're going.

07:38.791 --> 07:40.418
It's been
a trying season,

07:40.460 --> 07:42.253
but I am 4-1 in singles,

07:42.295 --> 07:45.465
and I was voted Academic
Athlete of the week.

07:47.008 --> 07:49.719
Is that all you're about?
Tennis?

07:49.760 --> 07:51.846
Is there nothing else?

07:51.888 --> 07:53.764
What's your 3-year plan?

07:53.806 --> 07:56.476
I don't know, but
I'm still a freshman,

07:56.517 --> 07:58.186
so, there's
still some time.

07:58.227 --> 08:00.271
OK. It's almost May.

08:00.313 --> 08:01.772
Do you even know what
you're doing this summer?

08:01.814 --> 08:05.109
I--I--
I didn't, but I...

08:05.151 --> 08:07.445
PKZ wants leaders, Simone.

08:07.487 --> 08:09.113
You have to think ahead.

08:09.155 --> 08:11.699
Plan, then execute.

08:11.741 --> 08:13.493
If you can't
or won't do that,

08:13.534 --> 08:15.244
then PKZ isn't for you.

08:15.286 --> 08:17.538
No, I'm PKZ material.
I just--

08:17.580 --> 08:19.874
You've been avoiding
my calls, texts, and emails.

08:19.916 --> 08:21.626
I was about to try
carrier pigeon next.

08:21.667 --> 08:23.878
Lando: Charlotte,
what are you doing here?

08:23.920 --> 08:25.046
I'm here for
the masquerade ball.

08:25.087 --> 08:26.339
Lando:
Wait. Simone?

08:26.380 --> 08:28.257
How do you know
my sister?

08:30.301 --> 08:32.261
And you clearly know
my brother.

08:36.849 --> 08:39.644
How well do you two
know each other?

08:41.354 --> 08:43.606
So, you don't have
any plans for the future,

08:43.648 --> 08:45.149
but your present is about

08:45.191 --> 08:47.193
breaking PKZ rules
while on line.

08:47.235 --> 08:48.903
Is that right?

08:54.992 --> 08:56.786
OK, instead of
terrorizing one of
your pledges,

08:56.827 --> 08:58.704
how about we get
to why you've been
blowing up my phone?

08:58.746 --> 09:02.250
You haven't submitted
any photos to apply for
the masquerade ball photo job.

09:02.291 --> 09:04.210
Lando: Yeah.
I texted, I emailed,

09:04.252 --> 09:05.836
and I'm
telling you in person:
I'm not interested.

09:05.878 --> 09:07.421
Simone: Wait. Lando,
you're a photographer?

09:07.463 --> 09:11.717
He is,
and a damn good one, too.

09:16.138 --> 09:19.308
Lando, these are
really good.

09:19.350 --> 09:21.352
See, Orlando?
Simone can see

09:21.394 --> 09:23.563
you have a natural talent
that you're letting
go to waste.

09:23.604 --> 09:25.606
I am using my talent
the way I see fit.

09:25.648 --> 09:27.233
Why is that
so hard to grasp?

09:27.275 --> 09:29.026
We'll continue this
later on.

09:29.068 --> 09:33.114
I have somewhere to be.
Simone, internship options.

09:33.155 --> 09:35.366
Be prepared to discuss
those later, too.

09:35.408 --> 09:37.368
Until then, try and get
my hard-headed brother

09:37.410 --> 09:39.829
to see reason.

09:43.874 --> 09:47.128
[Sighs]
Well, your sister is, uh...

09:47.169 --> 09:48.921
A lot. Yeah.

09:48.963 --> 09:50.881
Charlotte operates at
a 10 at all times.

09:50.923 --> 09:52.925
Well, I need to make
a good impression, so,

09:52.967 --> 09:55.177
she wants you to submit
these photos.

09:55.219 --> 09:57.138
Could you help
a sista out, please?

09:58.306 --> 10:01.309
Yeah, no can do. But...

10:01.350 --> 10:03.269
there was something
I wanted to give you.

10:03.311 --> 10:05.646
I know 'cause of
PKZ rules,

10:05.688 --> 10:07.898
you can't bring a date
to the ball, but, um...

10:08.983 --> 10:11.152
maybe you
can save me a dance.

10:11.193 --> 10:13.404
Definitely.

10:13.446 --> 10:16.115
[Pop music playing]
Keisha: Yes.

10:16.157 --> 10:17.867
[Cam chuckles]

10:17.908 --> 10:20.786
Keisha: OK. OK, we go
back around the other way.

10:20.828 --> 10:24.040
[Sighs]
We've been at this
for 30 minutes.

10:24.081 --> 10:26.292
Well, putting in the time
makes it perfect.

10:26.334 --> 10:29.462
You're stressing on it.
Your choreography
is fire, babe.

10:29.503 --> 10:30.963
There's a reason
why PKZ and KEK

10:31.005 --> 10:32.923
hired you
for this dance.

10:32.965 --> 10:34.592
It's just my first paid gig.
I just really
want it to be good.

10:34.634 --> 10:36.093
Let's try it one more time.

10:36.135 --> 10:37.762
OK.

10:37.803 --> 10:39.388
[Cell phone chimes]
Oh, hold up.

10:41.057 --> 10:42.975
Oh, I'm sorry, babe.
I gotta go.

10:43.017 --> 10:44.393
More KEK deliveries.

10:44.435 --> 10:46.103
I thought you
were done with that.

10:46.145 --> 10:47.605
I guess there's
a few more. I'm sorry.

10:47.647 --> 10:49.482
I'll catch you later
at dance rehearsal.

10:49.523 --> 10:50.858
-Yeah.
-OK.

10:55.279 --> 10:58.157
Good. You got my text,
and you're on time.

10:58.199 --> 10:59.784
Yeah, um,
you call it a text,

10:59.825 --> 11:01.202
I call it
emotional blackmail.

11:01.243 --> 11:02.620
All I said was
that it would mean

11:02.662 --> 11:04.163
a lot to
your big brother J.R.

11:04.205 --> 11:05.748
to have you
at the ball,

11:05.790 --> 11:08.459
and how he hasn't
asked anything of you

11:08.501 --> 11:10.544
since finding you again
after all these years.

11:10.586 --> 11:13.339
Yup, that's--that's
the emotional blackmail part.

11:13.381 --> 11:15.424
Whatever you
want to call it.

11:15.466 --> 11:16.926
You're here and
all you have to lose
is a fun night out.

11:16.967 --> 11:18.386
So, here's how
it's going down.

11:18.427 --> 11:20.012
You have 3 dates,

11:20.054 --> 11:21.806
3 locations,
30 minutes apiece.

11:21.847 --> 11:24.183
Wait. So, I only have
30 minutes to decide?

11:24.225 --> 11:25.893
Damon, the event
is tomorrow.

11:25.935 --> 11:27.728
You don't have time
to make a love connection.

11:27.770 --> 11:30.147
Date details are
now in your texts...
[Cell phone chimes]

11:30.189 --> 11:32.108
and you can
thank me later.

11:34.443 --> 11:35.945
Yeah. OK.

11:35.986 --> 11:40.116
Also, fix your face.
Vamonos.

11:40.157 --> 11:43.119
Woman: You're a Pisces?
Damon: Yeah.

11:43.160 --> 11:44.620
That's gonna be
a problem.

11:44.662 --> 11:46.205
I usually don't
vibe with Pisces.

11:46.247 --> 11:47.665
Sorry.

11:47.707 --> 11:49.291
Woman 2: My followers
don't play,

11:49.333 --> 11:51.293
so you're gonna have
to win them over, too.

11:51.335 --> 11:53.212
What do you like
most about me?

11:54.380 --> 11:56.549
I mean,
I just met you, so...

11:56.590 --> 11:58.759
So, who's your favorite
player of all time?

11:58.801 --> 12:00.511
The Griffeys,
of course.

12:00.553 --> 12:02.138
I mean, what other
father/son duo

12:02.179 --> 12:04.849
played together
in pro sports history?

12:04.890 --> 12:07.017
OK. I see you.

12:07.059 --> 12:08.769
All right.
Tell me your exact
time of birth,

12:08.811 --> 12:10.396
and I may be able
to salvage this

12:10.438 --> 12:11.981
if I know your moon
and rising.

12:12.022 --> 12:14.817
Uh, I don't know what time
I was born. Sorry.

12:14.859 --> 12:16.777
Well, can't you,
like, text your mom
or something?

12:16.819 --> 12:19.113
This is important.

12:19.155 --> 12:20.531
And...?

12:20.573 --> 12:22.450
You're confident.

12:22.491 --> 12:25.578
Wow! You already see
the real me.

12:25.619 --> 12:26.912
Y'all, drop a comment

12:26.954 --> 12:28.539
if you think we make
a cute couple.

12:28.581 --> 12:29.874
[Chuckles]

12:29.915 --> 12:30.916
Woman 3: I see you, too.

12:30.958 --> 12:32.543
Sub 2.00 ERA,

12:32.585 --> 12:34.670
leading the conference
in strikeouts,

12:34.712 --> 12:37.173
a WHIP of 0.89.

12:37.214 --> 12:38.883
So, you did
your research. Heh.

12:38.924 --> 12:41.844
Oh, yeah. And I can
upgrade you like Beyonce.

12:41.886 --> 12:44.221
But first we gotta
work on that curveball.

12:45.723 --> 12:47.183
Excuse me
for a second.

12:47.224 --> 12:48.225
Oh, yeah.

12:48.267 --> 12:50.352
Just--I got a text.

12:50.394 --> 12:51.896
♪ The world is yours ♪

12:51.937 --> 12:54.857
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh
oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

12:54.899 --> 12:56.650
♪ Tell me what you wanna do,
where you wanna go ♪

12:56.692 --> 12:58.944
♪ Said it's on you
if you don't know ♪

12:58.986 --> 13:00.905
♪ The world is yours ♪

13:00.946 --> 13:02.698
-♪ No stopping you ♪
-♪ The world is yours ♪

13:02.740 --> 13:05.159
-♪ No stopping you ♪
-♪ The world is yours ♪

13:20.174 --> 13:23.010
What's up with Damon
and discount Rihanna?

13:23.052 --> 13:25.387
I don't know.
I hadn't noticed.

13:25.429 --> 13:27.223
Mm-hmm. Then what
you're looking at

13:27.264 --> 13:29.433
must be real important.

13:29.475 --> 13:30.976
Well, I'm just wondering
how someone

13:31.018 --> 13:32.812
I used to eat for lunch is

13:32.853 --> 13:35.022
winning millions of dollars
on the pro circuit.

13:35.064 --> 13:37.858
Mm. Compare and despair
is a dangerous game.

13:37.900 --> 13:39.944
You're right
where you need to be,

13:39.985 --> 13:42.196
and when you
don't need to be here
anymore, you'll know.

13:42.238 --> 13:46.242
Yeah. You're a good friend.

13:46.283 --> 13:50.496
I know.
[Laughs]

13:50.538 --> 13:53.582
Nathaniel Hardin,
you have a very
special delivery.

13:53.624 --> 13:55.125
Who is this from?

13:55.167 --> 13:57.211
Mm-mm.

13:57.253 --> 13:59.922
[Sighs]
Ahem.

13:59.964 --> 14:01.632
"Dust off those
glass slippers

14:01.674 --> 14:03.676
"and bring
your best smile

14:03.717 --> 14:05.261
"'cause this
Prince Charming

14:05.302 --> 14:07.847
wants to see his
Cinderella's smile."

14:07.888 --> 14:09.849
He says
he'll be wearing
a rose in his lapel.

14:09.890 --> 14:11.809
Oh, that is so romantic,

14:11.851 --> 14:13.811
if you're into
that kind of thing.

14:13.853 --> 14:15.437
I really, really am.

14:17.064 --> 14:18.607
What would make it better

14:18.649 --> 14:20.901
is if you would come
to the ball with me.

14:23.737 --> 14:25.364
You know what? Whatever.

14:25.406 --> 14:26.866
I'm in. Let's do it.

14:26.907 --> 14:29.159
We're gonna eat
them girls up.

14:29.201 --> 14:30.786
-Yes!
-They not ready.

14:30.828 --> 14:32.288
Charlotte:
What about this one?

14:32.329 --> 14:34.456
You'd learn
sports marketing

14:34.498 --> 14:35.958
from agents
and retired
pro athletes.

14:36.000 --> 14:38.544
Uh...
[Exhales]

14:38.586 --> 14:40.462
I don't think marketing's
really my thing.

14:40.504 --> 14:43.299
I've given you 5 options
for summer internships,

14:43.340 --> 14:44.842
and none of them
are right?

14:44.884 --> 14:46.594
Simone, work with me.

14:46.635 --> 14:48.846
I know.
I'm trying, but I'm sorry.

14:48.888 --> 14:51.056
None of these
are speaking to me.

14:51.098 --> 14:55.102
Simone,
I'm a senior manager at
a Fortune 500 company.

14:55.144 --> 14:57.771
All I need to do is make
one call and you're in.

14:57.813 --> 14:59.523
Just pick something.

15:00.900 --> 15:02.234
Uh...

15:04.904 --> 15:06.614
At least tell me
which one of
Lando's photos

15:06.655 --> 15:09.408
you like best.

15:09.450 --> 15:12.119
Charlotte, I told you
he still said no.

15:12.161 --> 15:14.413
My brother
doesn't always know
what's best for him.

15:14.455 --> 15:16.248
He seemed
pretty clear to me.

15:18.334 --> 15:21.003
You know what?
I'm pulling rank.

15:21.045 --> 15:22.671
As your potential
big sister,

15:22.713 --> 15:24.924
help me pick out
photos to submit.

15:30.804 --> 15:32.514
Bro, so, you didn't like
any of the women

15:32.556 --> 15:34.016
Gabby sent your way?

15:34.058 --> 15:36.393
[Door closes]
No. I didn't.

15:36.435 --> 15:38.395
All you did was
waste Gabby's time.

15:38.437 --> 15:40.773
I told you that
I wasn't feeling
the masquerade ball.

15:40.814 --> 15:43.567
You want to tell me why?

15:43.609 --> 15:45.986
Hmm. Simone. You know
she's gonna be there,

15:46.028 --> 15:47.571
and you'd rather
sit around here

15:47.613 --> 15:49.323
and drown in
your feelings for her?

15:49.365 --> 15:51.450
Yeah, well, I'm drowning
because of you.

15:51.492 --> 15:53.077
What the hell
are you talkin' about?

15:53.118 --> 15:55.704
Your advice not to
tell Simone how I felt,

15:55.746 --> 15:57.206
that was trash, bro.

15:57.247 --> 15:59.667
Then why'd you listen?

15:59.708 --> 16:02.461
Exactly. 'Cause you know my
trash advice was the move.

16:02.503 --> 16:05.047
And getting out of this
funk and going to a dope
event is the move, too.

16:05.089 --> 16:07.299
You keep thinking that you
know what's best for me,

16:07.341 --> 16:09.885
and you just don't, J.,
all right?

16:09.927 --> 16:13.639
So, I'm gonna need
you just to stay out
of my business, bro.

16:13.681 --> 16:15.474
All right, bro.
You got it.

16:15.516 --> 16:18.686
[Door opens and closes]

16:25.567 --> 16:28.195
Oh, Ms. McCalla.
A moment?

16:28.237 --> 16:30.155
Keisha: Hi, Dr. Pace.
Dr. Pace: Is it true that

16:30.197 --> 16:31.699
you're choreographing
the dance for
the masquerade ball?

16:31.740 --> 16:33.701
Yeah, the planning
committee saw

16:33.742 --> 16:35.327
my Black Joy Day dance,

16:35.369 --> 16:36.870
and they thought
that I could bring

16:36.912 --> 16:38.580
a unique
perspective, so...

16:38.622 --> 16:40.749
As I'm sure you're aware,
professional choreographing

16:40.791 --> 16:42.710
outside of class
is against the rules.

16:42.751 --> 16:44.336
No, I know.
I just thought that

16:44.378 --> 16:45.838
since this was
a Bringston thing...

16:45.879 --> 16:49.008
Rules are rules,
no matter who it's for.

16:49.049 --> 16:51.844
Dr. Pace, I promise
nothing like this
will ever happen again.

16:51.885 --> 16:54.722
I know it won't,
because this is
the final straw.

16:54.763 --> 16:57.474
You've officially
failed my class.

16:57.516 --> 16:59.977
I hope this opportunity
is worth it.

17:11.030 --> 17:14.199
[Line ringing]

17:25.919 --> 17:27.463
[Knock on door,
door opens]

17:35.888 --> 17:38.348
PKZ offered me
the photographer job.

17:38.390 --> 17:41.060
Oh. Congrats.

17:41.101 --> 17:42.895
My guess,
Charlotte submitted

17:42.936 --> 17:45.147
my photos
behind my back.

17:45.189 --> 17:46.815
And please tell me
that you didn't have
anything to do with this.

17:46.857 --> 17:49.401
I maybe helped her
pick out some photos.

17:49.443 --> 17:50.903
After I specifically
said I wasn't interested.

17:50.944 --> 17:52.571
Lando, what was I
supposed to do?

17:52.613 --> 17:54.782
I need to make a good
impression with her.

17:54.823 --> 17:56.784
PKZ means a lot to me.

17:56.825 --> 17:59.536
So, if you get into PKZ,
is this how it's gonna be?

17:59.578 --> 18:01.580
You choosing what
Charlotte wants
over how I feel?

18:01.622 --> 18:04.083
Ain't nobody gonna
focus on you.
I'm gonna focus on me.

18:04.124 --> 18:05.834
Is this really
that deep to you?

18:05.876 --> 18:07.795
No one is forcing you
to take this job, Lando.

18:07.836 --> 18:09.546
Except they are.
Charlotte told
the whole family.

18:09.588 --> 18:11.090
Now everybody
pressuring me.

18:11.131 --> 18:13.050
Because they know you
love photography, Lando.

18:13.092 --> 18:14.968
Why won't you just
take a chance?

18:15.010 --> 18:16.678
Because sometimes
when your passion
becomes your profession,

18:16.720 --> 18:18.931
it changes it for you,
and I don't want that.

18:18.972 --> 18:20.641
You struggle with being
in the spotlight.

18:20.682 --> 18:22.726
Maybe your resistance
with sharing your work

18:22.768 --> 18:26.146
is because you're afraid
it'll bring attention
that you don't want.

18:26.188 --> 18:27.314
Wow.

18:30.192 --> 18:33.070
So, you go behind my back
and conspire with my sister

18:33.112 --> 18:34.738
to get me a job
I don't even want,

18:34.780 --> 18:36.573
and now you
psychoanalyzing me.

18:36.615 --> 18:38.450
Maybe you and Charlotte
really are sisters.

18:38.492 --> 18:40.619
[Scoffs]

18:40.661 --> 18:42.287
You know what?
I think I had enough

18:42.329 --> 18:45.040
of the Johnson
siblings today, so,

18:45.082 --> 18:48.168
if you don't mind,
I gotta go to
dance rehearsal.

19:00.722 --> 19:02.558
Cam: Hey, Lou, my guy,
your two left feet

19:02.599 --> 19:04.434
got you wobbling
out there.

19:04.476 --> 19:07.271
Wobble! That should be
your line name.

19:07.312 --> 19:10.190
OK, Milli Vanilli.
Get it?

19:10.232 --> 19:11.525
'Cause you can sing.

19:11.567 --> 19:14.027
Right. I can.
They couldn't.

19:14.069 --> 19:15.863
Perry: Bro, you dug deep
for that reference.

19:15.904 --> 19:18.282
How old are you really?
Cam: Right!

19:20.033 --> 19:23.370
Uh, Kesh. Hey.
You good?

19:23.412 --> 19:26.874
Yeah, I'm fine.
Let's run through it.

19:26.915 --> 19:29.543
5, 6, 7, 8.

19:32.212 --> 19:33.755
Cam, you're on
the wrong side.

19:33.797 --> 19:36.842
Cam: No, I'm not.
Keisha: Just do it again.

19:38.635 --> 19:40.846
5, 6, 7, 8.

19:44.308 --> 19:46.059
OK, you're a half a beat
too slow now.

19:47.728 --> 19:49.479
What the hell are you doing?

19:49.521 --> 19:51.190
Simone: No, it wasn't--
Keisha: Well, Maybe if you

19:51.231 --> 19:53.192
spent more time focusing
on learning the steps

19:53.233 --> 19:54.359
instead of playing around
with your little friends,

19:54.401 --> 19:55.903
it would look better.

19:55.944 --> 19:58.614
Keisha, I was the one
that messed up, not Cam.

19:58.655 --> 20:00.741
It's gonna be dope, OK?

20:03.827 --> 20:05.412
My bad. Y'all are--

20:06.538 --> 20:08.373
y'all are gonna be great.

20:08.415 --> 20:10.667
Simone's right. Um,

20:10.709 --> 20:12.377
I'll see all y'all later.

20:12.419 --> 20:14.504
Well, y'all can go.

20:19.426 --> 20:20.844
Cam, can I talk
to you real quick?

20:20.886 --> 20:22.804
Nah. I think you've
done that enough.

20:22.846 --> 20:24.640
Look, I don't know
what's going on with you,

20:24.681 --> 20:27.768
but whatever it is,
ain't it.

20:35.275 --> 20:38.695
Man: Dr. Amara Patterson,
you have a very, very
special delivery.

20:38.737 --> 20:40.781
Oh. Uh...

20:40.822 --> 20:42.366
[Chuckles]

20:42.407 --> 20:43.825
thank you.

20:58.757 --> 21:02.177
Thea: Well, that's
a beautiful dress, Dr. P.

21:02.219 --> 21:04.763
I guess fairy tales

21:04.805 --> 21:08.809
are for university
presidents, too.

21:08.850 --> 21:12.020
You know, Thea, I've been
meaning to check on you,

21:12.062 --> 21:13.814
but I didn't want
to intrude.

21:13.855 --> 21:17.526
I know this last semester
has been trying for you.

21:17.567 --> 21:19.194
If you ever need an ear...

21:19.236 --> 21:21.113
Thank you.

21:23.115 --> 21:24.825
Actually, I have--

21:24.866 --> 21:27.411
I've been wondering
about something.

21:27.452 --> 21:29.663
Sit.

21:29.705 --> 21:33.750
OK, so I've recovered
from my injury,

21:33.792 --> 21:36.586
and I'm playing the best
tennis of my life,

21:36.628 --> 21:40.299
and now I'm
contemplating
maybe going pro.

21:40.340 --> 21:42.175
Oh. That's a big step.

21:42.217 --> 21:45.679
Yeah. Ready
for another one?

21:45.721 --> 21:49.891
I've been working a lot
on this in therapy,

21:49.933 --> 21:52.602
and I'm
finally realizing

21:52.644 --> 21:54.104
that being
excellent in tennis

21:54.146 --> 21:55.605
doesn't have to
come at the cost

21:55.647 --> 21:57.524
of everything else
in my life,

21:57.566 --> 22:02.070
and I can
have love and be
the best on the court.

22:04.281 --> 22:07.284
I miss Damon...

22:07.326 --> 22:08.994
and I think
it was a mistake

22:09.036 --> 22:10.996
breaking up
with him,

22:11.038 --> 22:15.292
but telling him that
is really scary.

22:15.334 --> 22:18.170
I hear you,
but sometimes

22:18.211 --> 22:20.922
the things
worth fighting for are

22:20.964 --> 22:23.675
the very things
that scare us the most.

22:25.052 --> 22:27.679
[Doorknob rattles]

22:29.264 --> 22:31.433
Cam: Hey, bro,
what is that...

22:31.475 --> 22:33.435
workout number 3
today?

22:33.477 --> 22:35.103
Yeah. So?

22:35.145 --> 22:37.064
Well, clearly the latest
whatever with Simone

22:37.105 --> 22:38.940
is hitting different.

22:38.982 --> 22:41.068
[Scoffs]
Bro, you don't even know
what you're talking about.

22:41.109 --> 22:42.819
There was a kiss,
and then y'all

22:42.861 --> 22:45.030
just decided
to be friends.

22:45.072 --> 22:48.867
I hear Keisha and Nate
talk about y'all a lot.

22:48.909 --> 22:50.744
Yeah.

22:50.786 --> 22:52.412
Well, Keisha and Nate
don't know

22:52.454 --> 22:54.081
what they're
talking about

22:54.122 --> 22:56.375
because it's Simone who
just wants to be friends.

22:56.416 --> 22:58.043
You want more?

22:58.085 --> 22:59.669
Doesn't matter
what I want anymore,

22:59.711 --> 23:01.004
all right, Cam?

23:01.046 --> 23:02.089
That doesn't
sound healthy.

23:02.130 --> 23:03.590
Change of plans,
my guy.

23:03.632 --> 23:05.092
You punked out
a little.

23:05.133 --> 23:06.760
Tell Simone how
you really feel.

23:06.802 --> 23:08.053
Look, just because I'm going
through stuff right now

23:08.095 --> 23:09.596
does not mean that
I'm punking out.

23:09.638 --> 23:11.098
You ain't being
yourself for a minute.

23:11.139 --> 23:12.849
Stand in your truth.

23:12.891 --> 23:14.267
Let it never be said
that you

23:14.309 --> 23:16.061
didn't shoot
your shot honestly.

23:16.103 --> 23:17.604
The Damon Sims I know,

23:17.646 --> 23:19.564
the one who gets
on my damn nerve,

23:19.606 --> 23:21.733
speaks his mind.

23:21.775 --> 23:24.486
You're right, bro.

23:24.528 --> 23:27.864
I'm gonna tell her
how I feel when she
gets back from the ball.

23:27.906 --> 23:31.284
No. Don't wait.
Go to the ball.
Tell her there.

23:31.326 --> 23:32.911
I'm telling you,
once you step

23:32.953 --> 23:34.579
onto that
ballroom floor,

23:34.621 --> 23:36.832
it's gonna feel
like magic.

23:36.873 --> 23:38.625
[String quartet playing]

23:42.129 --> 23:44.756
Cam, voice-over: You're gonna
feel like anything is possible.

23:44.798 --> 23:46.800
Soak that in, bro.

23:46.842 --> 23:49.886
Embrace the magic because
you're not just telling her

23:49.928 --> 23:51.596
that you want to be with her,

23:51.638 --> 23:53.557
you're telling her that you want
a future together.

23:54.099 --> 23:57.144
Cam, voice-over: You'll know
when the moment is right.

23:57.185 --> 23:59.187
It'll be right there.

24:01.440 --> 24:04.317
Damon:
Excuse me, my lady.

24:04.359 --> 24:06.445
I must have the pleasure
of making your acquaintance.

24:06.486 --> 24:08.196
I'm Samuel.

24:10.157 --> 24:12.409
Hello. I'm...

24:13.535 --> 24:15.245
Desiree.

24:15.287 --> 24:18.039
Ah. Well, lovely
to meet you, Desiree.

24:19.541 --> 24:21.501
So, um, did you
come alone?

24:21.543 --> 24:23.086
-Afraid so...
-Mm.

24:23.128 --> 24:24.921
and I see you are
without a companion.

24:24.963 --> 24:27.674
Um, yes, for now,

24:27.716 --> 24:30.677
but I was hoping
to change that.

24:30.719 --> 24:32.554
I know we've
only just met,

24:32.596 --> 24:36.641
but when I think about
my life and my future...

24:39.269 --> 24:42.022
I see you in it.

24:42.063 --> 24:44.608
Well, that's a shame.

24:44.649 --> 24:47.736
Desiree is all for
living in the moment.

24:49.821 --> 24:51.573
Damon, you good?

24:51.615 --> 24:53.533
Yeah. I'm fine,
and that was Samuel.

24:53.575 --> 24:55.076
Hey, Simone,
we need you

24:55.118 --> 24:57.496
for the final run-through.

24:57.537 --> 25:00.081
Simone:
Oh. Um, well, it was
nice meeting you, Samuel.

25:00.123 --> 25:03.084
Uh, you, too, Des--
Desiree.

25:09.841 --> 25:12.928
♪ That is
good enough for me ♪

25:12.969 --> 25:14.262
♪ I think we
both agree... ♪

25:14.304 --> 25:16.806
Well, you both look
very beautiful.

25:16.848 --> 25:18.225
So do you.

25:18.266 --> 25:20.185
Enough to justify
these heels?

25:20.227 --> 25:21.686
Totally.

25:21.728 --> 25:24.064
OK. Well, if
you'll excuse me,

25:24.105 --> 25:25.941
I have to go
find someone.

25:25.982 --> 25:28.610
♪ ...you in my grip... ♪

25:28.652 --> 25:31.238
Well, you ready to find
your mystery man?

25:31.279 --> 25:33.573
Oh, there's no point.

25:33.615 --> 25:36.284
Everybody here has
flowers on their lapel.

25:39.079 --> 25:41.540
-Oh.
-Ohh.

25:41.581 --> 25:44.417
-Another one?
-Another one.

25:47.003 --> 25:49.089
"Roses are red.
Violets are blue.

25:49.130 --> 25:51.424
"Find the flowers
on my mask.

25:51.466 --> 25:53.426
I'm waiting
for you."

25:53.468 --> 25:57.138
OK. Go get your man.

25:57.180 --> 26:00.100
Imma go
get him, girl. Mm!

26:00.141 --> 26:02.394
Ha ha!

26:02.435 --> 26:04.187
You haven't said a word
to Damon all night.

26:04.229 --> 26:06.022
The way you've been
staring at him,

26:06.064 --> 26:07.274
you better hope your face
don't freeze that way.

26:07.315 --> 26:09.484
What's up?

26:09.526 --> 26:12.028
Well, apparently, I
gave him trash advice
about his love life.

26:12.070 --> 26:13.655
Now, you know I need
more details than that.

26:15.240 --> 26:17.409
His feelings
for Simone resurfaced
in a major way,

26:17.450 --> 26:19.202
and I told him,
"Put that on ice."

26:19.244 --> 26:21.037
His dad just passed,
plus a relationship

26:21.079 --> 26:22.664
going wrong with
Damon and Simone

26:22.706 --> 26:24.499
would wreck our
Bringston friend family.

26:24.541 --> 26:27.127
But you don't know if it
would've gone wrong or not,

26:27.168 --> 26:29.337
and it's really
not your business...

26:29.379 --> 26:30.922
-Well--
-And, finally...

26:30.964 --> 26:32.465
What was that for?

26:32.507 --> 26:34.426
For not telling me the tea
on Damon and Simone.

26:34.467 --> 26:36.553
If I had known, I would've
never tried to fix him up.

26:36.595 --> 26:38.305
Why not? You were just
trying to help him out.

26:38.346 --> 26:41.141
Leaving Damon alone
is the best way
to help him out.

26:41.182 --> 26:43.393
Plus, the way he's been
staring at Simone tonight,

26:43.435 --> 26:45.312
that's something
deeper than heartbreak.

26:45.353 --> 26:47.188
Now, make things
right with Damon

26:47.230 --> 26:49.649
before the face he's
making at you freezes.

26:49.691 --> 26:52.777
♪ Oh oh ♪

26:52.819 --> 26:54.529
♪ Ooh ooh ♪

26:56.656 --> 26:58.533
♪ I know what you've
been feeling ♪

26:58.575 --> 27:01.202
♪ For a long time ♪

27:01.244 --> 27:03.872
♪ Time... ♪

27:03.913 --> 27:07.459
Thea:
Hey, can we talk?

27:08.710 --> 27:12.255
Uh, you look...
amazing. Heh.

27:12.297 --> 27:14.883
Thank you.

27:16.718 --> 27:18.678
Uh, heh.
Do you want to...?
Come on.

27:18.720 --> 27:20.805
Yeah. Heh heh.

27:23.224 --> 27:28.271
So I have been
thinking a lot

27:28.313 --> 27:29.773
about my life

27:29.814 --> 27:33.109
and, um, what
I want out of it

27:33.151 --> 27:37.822
and if I've made
the right decisions.

27:37.864 --> 27:39.741
Someone like you,
when they make decisions,

27:39.783 --> 27:41.743
they don't look back.

27:41.785 --> 27:44.829
Someone like that lives
their life with no regrets.

27:44.871 --> 27:48.500
Our breakup, I think
that was a mistake.

27:48.541 --> 27:50.794
I mean, I know you
had your reasons.

27:50.835 --> 27:53.963
Yeah, and at the time,
those reasons felt right,

27:54.005 --> 27:56.549
but not anymore.

27:56.591 --> 28:00.470
I'm just not in the right
headspace for this.

28:00.512 --> 28:03.682
A lot has changed for me...

28:03.723 --> 28:05.308
-Oh, I know.
-in the past two weeks, and--

28:05.350 --> 28:07.268
I know, I know.

28:07.310 --> 28:09.604
You dad just died,
and I can help
you through that.

28:09.646 --> 28:14.150
Look, hey, it's not
just that, all right? I'm--

28:14.192 --> 28:17.445
I'm dealing with
a lot right now, Thea.

28:17.487 --> 28:19.489
I think it's important

28:19.531 --> 28:21.950
that I process
all of it for myself,

28:21.991 --> 28:25.578
but I will always
care about you, Thea,

28:25.620 --> 28:27.956
but I think you made
the right call.

28:38.466 --> 28:40.593
Man: All right, all right,
everybody.

28:40.635 --> 28:43.638
The masquerade dance performance
is starting now.

28:43.680 --> 28:46.391
